script = ExtResource("3_771u1")
category = 1
text = "The Legendary Giras are a position granted to the 4 strongest pirate crews in the Sugori Isles, by the Mala who is currently Vanessa Haliness. Giras despite having no political qualification remain a strong part of the government tied solely by tradition and need for strong military power. The current Giras are \"Sword of the Seas\" Gus, \"Boxing Villain\" Morgan V. Pikefist, \"Bullet God\" Yves von Eric and \"Blood Fiend\" Gorgana Wretchirl. As the Giras are a tradition, it was not a thing from the beginning of the countries system and instead became a feature of the government due to the \"Great Pirate Era\" around 350 years ago.

This Great Pirate Era started even before the reign of Halina the Pirate. This was a time when the Sugori were quite a villainous nation, with fairly selfish intentions and the more common perception of \"pirates\". Pirates that were known in the country were usually locally known, with few exceptions ever so often of pirates being known at a wider scale. Yet this all changed when paths merged of 3 great pirate crews. The Eagle Pirates, Momodare Pirates and Blue Boon Pirates which all were known by the majority of the nation. Each of these crews had legends and myths, and celebrities for their captains, who all were scarily strong individuals. These 3 crews due to existing at the same time, creating a power balance known as the 3 Legendary Giras, a name given to solely them, but the people started calling any future prodigies the same, and eventually it stuck.

The Momodare Pirates were led by \"Vigorous Plantsman\" Pete Momodare, a travelling botanist. Momodare led a crew of scientists and doctors that explored to research plant life of other nations but grew in fame due to the strength of their crew. Momodare was a diamond in the rough as he was quite a modest and selfless individual. Many thought down on him because of it, but for others it inspired them to explore the seas without looting or pillaging and instead for the good of themselves or others.
The Eagle Pirates were led by \"The Golden\" Vincent Hans Gregory, a noble of a rich Capital family that decided to instead become a pirate. Quite bored of his life in the city, Gregory sailed the seas and created a scary pirate crew that was largely pretty powerful. Gregory reached fame status after he conquered nearby islands himself and took over countries in Pustan with just his own fleet, something so impressive that the monarch of one of the kingdoms respected him and gave him shares of the gold as a deal. He was a self-acclaimed conqueror who found interest and excitement in one-upping himself round every corner.
Lastly is the Blue Boon Pirates led by Aquilo Brolluc the \"Lunatic Lumberjack\", an ex-carpenter turnt pirate who was known for his lack of sanity. Aquilo is from the aquited like of the Brolluc Carpenters who are nationally famous for their continuously impressive work for the Malas.

The Legendary Giras were just a group of pirates that the public fantasized into a group of strong pirates with foundation, and it developed into a system that leads many young children to want to venture the seas. After local news found out about a Gira retiring from piracy, people would always speculate who will fill their spot next. Then around 200 years ago, despite the Giras being anywhere from 2-6 people, it finally got finalised into the government, and 4 Giras was the number set in stone no matter what."
id = 56
name = "Legendary Gira"
gdscript = ExtResource("1_6c56y")
